  "prompt": "What is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Cherokee County AL?",
  "response": "When looking for a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center in Cherokee County, AL, one option to consider is the following:\n\n**The Bridge, Inc. \u2013 Cedar Lodge**\n- **Location:** 402 Arnold Street NE, Fort Payne, AL 35967 (this is just outside Cherokee County but within a reasonable distance)\n- **Services Offered:** The Bridge, Inc. provides comprehensive substance abuse treatment services, including inpatient residential treatment. Their Cedar Lodge facility focuses on helping individuals recover from drug and alcohol addiction through a structured and supportive environment.\n- **Program Details:** Their program typically includes individual and group therapy, life skills training, and aftercare planning to support long-term recovery.\n- **Contact:** You can reach them at (256) 845-7767 for more information or to discuss admission.\n\nIt's essential to consider the specific needs of the individual seeking treatment, such as the type of substance use, any co-occurring mental health issues, and personal preferences when choosing a rehab center. It might also be helpful to check if the facility accepts your insurance or offers any financial assistance.\n\nAdditionally, you might want to consider other nearby options or broader statewide resources:\n\n- **Alabama Department of Mental Health Substance Abuse Services:** This state agency can provide information on other rehab centers and resources throughout Alabama. Their contact number is (334) 242-3454.\n\n- **SAMHSA Treatment Locator:** The Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration offers an online treatment locator that can help find additional facilities in and around Cherokee County. You can access it at [findtreatment.gov](https://findtreatment.gov).\n\nAlways verify the accreditation and licensing of any rehab center to ensure it meets the necessary standards of care.",
